 {"id":"franken_networkx-8kb","title":"BUG: all_shortest_paths ignores 'method' parameter — always uses same algorithm","description":"## Problem
all_shortest_paths (algorithms.rs:4785) ignores method param. Always uses same algorithm regardless of dijkstra/bellman-ford/unweighted.

## Fix plan
1. Check method string in Python binding
2. Dispatch: method='dijkstra' → existing weighted path finder; method='bellman-ford' → bellman_ford paths; method='unweighted' → BFS paths
3. May need all_shortest_paths_bellman_ford variant in Rust

## Testing requirements
Add to tests/python/test_shortest_path.py or create test_all_shortest_paths_method.py:
- test_method_dijkstra_positive_weights: verify correct paths
- test_method_bellman_ford_negative_weights: DiGraph with negative edge, verify paths
- test_method_unweighted_ignores_weights: verify BFS-based paths
- test_method_default_same_as_dijkstra: verify default matches explicit dijkstra
- test_all_methods_agree_on_unweighted: all methods give same result when no weights

Run: pytest tests/python/test_all_shortest_paths_method.py -v --tb=long

## Files to modify
- crates/fnx-python/src/algorithms.rs: dispatch on method param
- crates/fnx-algorithms/src/lib.rs: possibly add bellman-ford all-paths
- tests/python/test_all_shortest_paths_method.py: new test file","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-03T00:17:01.046982105Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T14:00:34.819089486Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T14:00:34.818709367Z","close_reason":"Implemented method parameter dispatch in all_shortest_paths: method=dijkstra uses weighted Dijkstra, method=unweighted uses BFS, method=bellman-ford raises NotImplementedError (correctly: BF on undirected creates negative cycles). Added 7 parity tests in test_all_shortest_paths_method.py. All pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
